  "A civil engineer needs to build a bridge across a gorge. She measures angles from two points 80 m apart on one rim to a point on the opposite rim: 72° and 63°. How wide is the gorge (distance from the closer measurement point to the opposite point)?": "",
  "About 65 m": "",
  "About 80 m": "",
  "About 120 m": "",
  "About 98 m": "",
  "Third angle = 180° − 72° − 63° = 45°. By Law of Sines: d/sin 63° = 80/sin 45°. d = 80 sin 63°/sin 45° ≈ 80(0.891)/0.707 ≈ 100.8 m. Closest is about 98 m.": "",
  "A telecommunications tower needs three equally-spaced guy wires. Each wire attaches at 40 m height and anchors 20 m from the base. What is the total length of wire needed?": "",
